The paper discusses a new approach to Approximate Query Processing (AQP) that leverages generative models learned over the complete database to answer SQL queries at interactive speeds. This topic falls under the database community, which is covered by the cs.DB sub-category. The use of generative models also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the techniques presented for query optimization and data cleaning, which are covered by the data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories, respectively.
